# AI Pinball Lookup

# Machine Instance API Deployment Guide (AWS CLI)

This document describes how to deploy the **Customer → Machine Instance system** for the **AI Pinball Lookup backend** using AWS CLI.

The instance system allows the platform to track **real physical pinball machines owned by customers**.

---

# Architecture

```
Client
   ↓
API Gateway
   ↓
AWS Lambda (ai-pinball-lookup)
   ↓
DynamoDB (pinball_machine_instances)
```

This system enables:

- tracking real machines
- linking machines to customers
- querying machines by owner or model
- future service history tracking

---

# 1. Authenticate

Login using AWS SSO.

```bash
aws sso login --profile dev
```

---

# 2. Create DynamoDB Table

Create the table used to store machine instances.

```bash
aws dynamodb create-table \
--table-name pinball_machine_instances \
--attribute-definitions \
AttributeName=instanceId,AttributeType=S \
AttributeName=customerId,AttributeType=S \
AttributeName=machineId,AttributeType=S \
--key-schema \
AttributeName=instanceId,KeyType=HASH \
--billing-mode PAY_PER_REQUEST \
--global-secondary-indexes \
'[
{
  "IndexName": "customerId-index",
  "KeySchema": [
    {"AttributeName": "customerId", "KeyType": "HASH"}
  ],
  "Projection": {
    "ProjectionType": "ALL"
  }
},
{
  "IndexName": "machineId-index",
  "KeySchema": [
    {"AttributeName": "machineId", "KeyType": "HASH"}
  ],
  "Projection": {
    "ProjectionType": "ALL"
  }
}
]' \
--region eu-central-1 \
--profile dev
```

Verify the table:

```bash
aws dynamodb describe-table \
--table-name pinball_machine_instances \
--region eu-central-1 \
--profile dev
```

---

# 3. Create API Gateway Routes

Create the **instances collection route**.

```bash
aws apigatewayv2 create-route \
--api-id cp114tpb2i \
--route-key "ANY /instances" \
--target "integrations/qe17036" \
--region eu-central-1 \
--profile dev
```

Create the **single instance route**.

```bash
aws apigatewayv2 create-route \
--api-id cp114tpb2i \
--route-key "ANY /instances/{id}" \
--target "integrations/qe17036" \
--region eu-central-1 \
--profile dev
```

Verify routes:

```bash
aws apigatewayv2 get-routes \
--api-id cp114tpb2i \
--region eu-central-1 \
--profile dev
```

---

# 4. Allow API Gateway to Invoke Lambda

Lambda must explicitly allow API Gateway to call it.

Allow `/instances`:

```bash
aws lambda add-permission \
--function-name ai-pinball-lookup \
--statement-id apigw-invoke-instances \
--action lambda:InvokeFunction \
--principal apigateway.amazonaws.com \
--source-arn "arn:aws:execute-api:eu-central-1:465443875879:cp114tpb2i/*/*/instances" \
--region eu-central-1 \
--profile dev
```

Allow `/instances/{id}`:

```bash
aws lambda add-permission \
--function-name ai-pinball-lookup \
--statement-id apigw-invoke-instances-id \
--action lambda:InvokeFunction \
--principal apigateway.amazonaws.com \
--source-arn "arn:aws:execute-api:eu-central-1:465443875879:cp114tpb2i/*/*/instances/*" \
--region eu-central-1 \
--profile dev
```

Check Lambda policy:

```bash
aws lambda get-policy \
--function-name ai-pinball-lookup \
--region eu-central-1 \
--profile dev
```

