# 5. Grant Lambda Access to DynamoDB

Create `instances-policy.json`.

```json
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Sid": "PinballMachineInstancesAccess",
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "dynamodb:GetItem",
        "dynamodb:PutItem",
        "dynamodb:UpdateItem",
        "dynamodb:Scan",
        "dynamodb:Query"
      ],
      "Resource": [
        "arn:aws:dynamodb:eu-central-1:465443875879:table/pinball_machine_instances",
        "arn:aws:dynamodb:eu-central-1:465443875879:table/pinball_machine_instances/index/*"
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

Attach the policy to the Lambda role:

```bash
aws iam put-role-policy \
--role-name ai-pinball-lookup-role-2vqd25c7 \
--policy-name PinballMachineInstancesAccess \
--policy-document file://instances-policy.json \
--profile dev
```

Verify:

```bash
aws iam get-role-policy \
--role-name ai-pinball-lookup-role-2vqd25c7 \
--policy-name PinballMachineInstancesAccess \
--profile dev
```

